 241  * ELECTRICITY PLANNING MODEL (EPM)
 242  * Developed at the World Bank
 243  **********************************************************************
 244  * Description:
 245  * This GAMS-based model is designed for electricity system planning,
 246  * incorporating capacity expansion, generation dispatch, and policy
 247  * constraints such as renewable energy targets, emissions reductions,
 248  * and market mechanisms.
 249  *
 250  * Author(s): ESMAP Modelling Team
 251  * Organization: World Bank
 252  * Version:
 253  * License: Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal
 254  *
 255  * Key Features:
 256  * - Optimization of electricity generation and capacity planning
 257  * - Inclusion of renewable energy integration and storage technologies
 258  * - Multi-period, multi-region modeling framework
 259  * - CO2 emissions constraints and policy instruments
 260  *
 261  * Notes:
 262  * - Ensure GAMS is installed before running this model.
 263  * - The model requires input data in .GDX.
 264  *
 265  * Contact:
 266  * Claire Nicolas, cnicolas@worldbank.org
 267  **********************************************************************
